## Official Development Model

Specify is the canonical orchestrator for non-trivial work in this repository.

- Start with `{{WORKFLOW_ENTRYPOINT}} <brief>` whenever possible
- If `{{WORKFLOW_ENTRYPOINT}}` is not available, start with `/speckit.specify` and continue through the Specify flow
- Use `BRIEF.md` as the default input source when the brief already exists in the repo
- Canonical feature artifacts live in `{{ARTIFACT_DIR}}/<feature-branch>/`
- Legacy PRD/SPEC flows are not the source of truth

### Official Workflow

1. Capture the brief from the user or `BRIEF.md`
2. Run `/speckit.specify`
3. Run `/speckit.clarify` when critical ambiguity remains
4. Run `/speckit.plan`
5. Run `/speckit.tasks`
6. Run `/speckit.analyze`
7. Run `/speckit.implement`
8. Run validation gates
9. Run a mandatory fix round
10. Re-run validation gates
11. Update `TEST_REPORT.md`
12. Update `REVIEW_REPORT.md`
13. Generate `SNAPSHOT.md` as the last step

The workflow must stop only when:

- critical ambiguity remains unresolved after clarification
- a new technology outside the approved stack is required
- an objective gate fails and cannot be resolved automatically

